  "name": "us-water-quality-data",
  "description": "Open dataset and tooling for U.S. drinking water quality at the ZIP-code level. Aggregates 49+ federal and state sources (EPA SDWIS, EPA ECHO, UCMR5, Consumer Confidence Reports, state MCL databases, CDC blood lead, FEMA flood claims, Census ACS, USGS groundwater) into a unified ZIP-level dataset with violation history, lead/copper sampling, PFAS detection, radon zone classification, flood risk, and a composite Home Safety Score for 41,000+ U.S. ZIP codes.",
